# ── Build-time, public (embedded in client bundle) ────────────────────────
# Set in Cloudflare Pages → Settings → Environment variables → Production
# (and Preview). Safe to expose; this is the public site key.
PUBLIC_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=

# ── Runtime, server-only (accessed via platform.env in handlers) ──────────
# Set in Cloudflare Pages → Settings → Environment variables → Production.
# Do NOT put in wrangler.toml. Required for Turnstile verification.
TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY=

# ── Manual Cloudflare dashboard configuration (no env var; reminder) ──────
# Required hardening, set in the CF dashboard, not in code:
#   1. Security → WAF → Rate Limiting Rules
#        Rule 1: POST /submit/* → 10 req / 60s per IP → block 10 min
#        Rule 2: POST /api/reports → 60 req / 60s per IP → block 5 min
#   2. Security → Bots → Bot Fight Mode: ON
#   3. Security → WAF → Managed Rules: enable Cloudflare Managed Ruleset
#   4. Zero Trust → Access → Application: cover /admin/* with email auth
